    "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Nehemiah 7 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:1",
      "text": "Now when the wall had been built and I had set up the doors, and the gatekeepers, the singers, and the Levites had been appointed,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:2",
      "text": "I gave my brother Hanani and Hananiah the governor of the castle charge over Jerusalem, for he was a more faithful and God-fearing man than many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:3",
      "text": "And I said to them, “Let not the gates of Jerusalem be opened until the sun is hot; and while they are still standing guard let them shut and bar the doors. Appoint guards from among the inhabitants of Jerusalem, each to his station and each opposite his own house.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:4",
      "text": "The city was wide and large, but the people within it were few and no houses had been built.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:5",
      "text": "Then God put it into my mind to assemble the nobles and the officials and the people to be enrolled by genealogy. And I found the book of the genealogy of those who came up at the first, and I found written in it:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:6",
      "text": "These were the people of the province who came up out of the captivity of those exiles whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried into exile; they returned to Jerusalem and Judah, each to his town.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:7",
      "text": "They came with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, Baanah. The number of the men of the people of Israel:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:8",
      "text": "the sons of Parosh, two thousand a hundred and seventy-two.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
