    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.61",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:61",
      "text": "The following were those who came up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub, Addon, and Immer, but they could not prove their fathers' houses nor their descent, whether they belonged to Israel:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.62",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:62",
      "text": "the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, the sons of Nekoda, six hundred and forty-two.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.63",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:63",
      "text": "Also, of the priests: the sons of Hobaiah, the sons of Hakkoz, the sons of Barzillai (who had taken a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite and was called by their name).",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.64",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:64",
      "text": "These sought their registration among those enrolled in the genealogies, but it was not found there, so they were excluded from the priesthood as unclean;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.65",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:65",
      "text": "the governor told them that they were not to partake of the most holy food, until a priest with Urim and Thummim should arise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.66",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:66",
      "text": "The whole assembly together was forty-two thousand three hundred and sixty,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:nehemiah.7.67",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "nehemiah",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 67,
      "referenceLabel": "Nehemiah 7:67",
      "text": "besides their menservants and maidservants, of whom there were seven thousand three hundred and thirty-seven; and they had two hundred and forty-five singers, male and female.",
      "paragraphStart": false
